         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">6/6/78. ¶  ¶ Allow me to ask you, dear and venerable M. Boissier, whether you could mention to me the principal  ¶ fodder-herbs ¶  and  ¶ nutritive ¶   ¶ grasses ¶  (4) of the pasturage of the Orient....</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">78.06.06</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Edmond Boissier</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Conservatoire et Jardin botanique, Geneva.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See also M to E. Boissier, 12 July 1875.</p>
               </note>6/6/78.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Allow me to ask you, dear and venerable M. Boissier, whether you could mention to me the principal <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">fodder-herbs</hi>
               </seg> and <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">nutritive</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">grasses</hi>
               </seg> (4) of the pasturage of the Orient.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am eager to issue a new edition of my select plants, of which work assuredly a copy exists in Genève,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B76.12.04.</p>
               </note> in this new edition<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B80.13.07.</p>
               </note> I like to include any important utilitarian plants of your <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">grand</hi>
               </seg> "Flora orientalis",<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Boissier (1867-88). The first three volumes of this work and the first part of the fourth volume were in print by 1878.</p>
               </note> which I may have omitted in the early issue of my work.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You will have observed, that I give due <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">credit</hi>
               </seg> to any one, who favors me with notes. I fancy, that many of the Astragali Trifolii &amp;c are there of highly pastoral value</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me hope, that young Mons. Boissier is making good progress with his monography of <name key="Epilobium">Epilobium</name>.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">An error for Boissier's son-in-law William Barbey who published an atlas of 25 plates illustrating <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Epilobium">Epilobium</name>
                     </seg> (Barbey (1885))? </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful remembrance</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
